A fire engulfed one of the world's tallest residential skyscrapers in Dubai on Friday, forcing hundreds of residents to rush out of a seventy-nine-story structure with a 337-meter high ground.
This is the second fire to sweep through the high-rise building – which coincidentally is called the "Torch" – in two years.
