Irina Burmistrova: "Guess why you can't get international rights in Moscow?"
That's right, because all traffic police departments ran out of forms.
Elena Podkolzina: "A question for knowledgeable people!"
We need to get international rights very urgently.
In Moscow, all the time is packed far ahead, on the spot coupons are not issued at all (there is a button, but they cannot give a coupon).
It seems that the portal of public services shows that in St. Petersburg there is no free time before the fig.
Has anyone tried to get in another city?
Work?
As explained in the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation, the requirements for the forms of international driver's licenses have changed, therefore, new forms are supplied to the units of the State Traffic Safety Inspectorate.
This may be related to the deficit, however, it is unclear what changes are in question, this has not been reported before.
The forms are purchased by the Special Purpose Center for Road Safety (TsSN BDD) of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation and then supply them to the traffic police units.
In recent years, all contracts have been concluded with Goznak JSC: in 2014-2015, almost 200 thousand IDP forms were manufactured, in 2016 15 thousand forms were purchased, in 2017 - 90 thousand, but the last contract was concluded on July 18 with LLC "First Printing Yard" for the production of 70 thousand forms.
There is a version that the CSN simply did not have time to hold the tender on time, which is why there was a shortage.
However, there are other versions of the shortage of forms: because of the crisis, many people began to independently travel not to Europe, but to cheaper Asian countries - China, Thailand and so on.
What rights are accepted there is not completely clear, that's why people are reinsured, which is why there was a rush demand for international "crusts".
Recently it became known that professional drivers will have to pass an exam to confirm their qualifications.
This proposal was made by the Ministry of Transport.
The international driving permit (IDP) of the new sample is valid from May 31, 2011.
