How did that work?
Three months later, Kelly tries to do the same.
He may prove to be a more effective manager than Priebus, but Trump still has an impulsive nature and his aides are still fighting each other for influence.
These constant factors make Kelly's task very difficult.
Tyumen Prosecutor's Office fights HIV dissident
The prosecutor's office challenged the decision of the Kalininsky District Court of Tyumen, which terminated the criminal case against a local resident whose young daughter died of HIV.
According to the investigation, the child died due to the fact that the mother is an HIV dissident and refused treatment.
However, the court acquitted her of responsibility in connection with reconciliation with the injured father.
The prosecutor's office believes that the crime cannot be left unpunished, so as not to create a precedent for other HIV dissidents.
The case against a resident of Tyumen was initiated under Part 1 of Art. 109 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (causing death by negligence) in April - after her three-year-old daughter died of HIV infection of stage 4B.
According to the prosecutor's office, the mother herself is HIV-positive.
"The woman was not treated herself and refused to treat her daughter, believing that HIV infection does not exist," the prosecutor's office of the Tyumen region explained.
The criminal case was submitted to the Kalininsky District Court of Tyumen, which on July 25 decided to terminate it.
A petition for this was filed by the father of the deceased girl, explaining that "he forgave his wife, has no claims against her, she made amends and apologized."
The prosecutor's office did not agree with the court's decision and appealed, demanding to cancel the decision to dismiss the case and send it for a new trial.
The girl died, and it is impossible to make amends for the harm caused by the crime.
The HIV-infected mother, contrary to the recommendations of doctors, refused to examine the baby and treat her for a dangerous infection," the press service of the prosecutor's office said.
According to the supervisory authority, she must be punished, otherwise other HIV dissidents will follow her example.
According to the Tyumen AIDS Center, now in the Tyumen region about 12 children with HIV do not receive medical care due to the refusal of their parents.
"And this situation has already improved - for a year of work of the special group, half of the parents who categorically refused to treat children with HIV changed their minds - they allowed them to diagnose, began to take drugs," said Elena Loseva, press secretary of the AIDS Center.
According to her, it is impossible to influence parents in a legislative way, and as a result, not all HIV-infected children can be detected - mothers do not allow them to be examined, hide, run away with children from hospitals.
What danger do HIV dissidents pose?
At the end of last year, St. Petersburg sociologists presented the results of the first study in Russia of the so-called movement of HIV dissidents.
HIV dissidents are people who deny the existence of HIV and refuse to take medication.
Doctors and activists of AIDS-service NGOs call such views anti-medical, and in their spread they see a serious threat.
A terrible photo shoot, which ended in tragedy, occurred on Thursday, August 3, at the Grechany railway station in Khmelnitsky.
