The Bruins have to exercise longer due to the fact that the National Collegiate Athletic Association canceled training twice a day.
The time is approaching eleven in the evening; a crowd of soccer players from the University of California, Los Angeles, lingers to chat on one side of the team's new training fields located on campus.
Some of them pulled down their T-shirts, exposing their backs, glistening with sweat after the tense first day of sports camp.
