Among other claims, there was criticism of the Central Bank, which, according to Tosunyan, does not always justifiably revoke licenses from some banks, which, however, was opposed by a representative of the Central Bank: many heads of the penalized banks, in particular, Vneshprombank, were members of the governing bodies of the ARB.
Apparently, this exchange of mutually exclusive views in a very sensitive banking environment with the main regulator became a visible reason for the fifteen largest banks, having declared disagreement with the policy of the ARB, to begin to prepare for joining the Association "Russia", noting that "the effectiveness of the ARB will be at a low level, and a constructive dialogue within the banking community is actually not carried out."
