In terms of personnel and organization, obviously, no special shocks are expected either.
Undoubtedly, ARB finds itself in a difficult financial and managerial situation after it loses such powerful and influential participants with their contributions and lobbying opportunities.
However, in this oldest - established in 1991 - organization that defends the interests of the banking community, there is considerable potential in order to continue to improve banking legislation and the sphere of monetary circulation as a whole.
It cannot be said that the Rossiya Association is ready to accept new members on any terms with open arms, judging by the reaction of its head, Anatoly Aksakov ("maybe they want too much"), who on July 21 at a briefing in the press center of the Parliamentary Gazette, said that "literally the next day, representatives of the banks that left the ARB asked me to consider the possibility of increasing the potential of our association "Russia"."
Their proposals are to strengthen the voice of bankers in the Association Council, as well as to pay more attention to new banking technologies.
Now the negotiation process is underway, the proposals of both sides are being studied, the agenda of the extraordinary congress of the association, which will be held in Sochi in mid-September as part of the international banking forum, is being prepared.
We'll decide there.
Also, Anatoly Aksakov, stressing that "he does not hold on to the chair", called a possible new head of the renewed association "Russia" Georgy Luntovsky, who leaves the post of Deputy Chairman of the Central Bank in September, highly describing his business and human qualities.
On August 18, Anatoly Aksakov, who is currently on vacation in Crimea, plans to interrupt his vacation for one day and arrive in Moscow for an extraordinary meeting of the Association Council "Russia", where it is planned to consider the agenda of the extraordinary congress of "Russia".
