Democracy in Afghanistan depends on the role of women in politics, the UN said.
Elections can only be representative when they involve all members of society, including women, the head of the U.N. mission in Afghanistan said Wednesday.
According to Nicholas Haysom, the current head of the UN assistance mission in Afghanistan, hundreds of women are running for provincial council elections, three women are vying for vice president, and more than 30 percent of the newly registered voters are women.
