Of these, 314 people were detained for illegally crossing the border, and the rest for violating the rules of residence of foreigners in Ukraine and other offenses.
The largest number - 717 illegal migrants were detained at the border with Moldova.
At the border with the EU countries, 272 illegal immigrants were detained, most of them on the border with Slovakia, Poland, Hungary and Romania.
According to statistics, among the detained illegal migrants are mainly citizens of Moldova, Russia, Georgia, Turkey, Azerbaijan, Bangladesh, Vietnam, India and Armenia.
In addition, almost 2,000 potential illegal migrants were not allowed into Ukraine.
Recall that the EU found an unusual way to get rid of migrants.
Jazz in Skolkovo: Experiment and Improvisation
The program of the second Skolkovo Jazz Science festival, which will be held on August 26 at the Skolkovo Innovation Center, has been announced.
Guests can expect performances of leading jazz groups and soloists, scientific discussions, interactive platforms and other musical and intellectual events.
As the organizers promise, the site will become a territory of improvisation and a field for demonstrating new creative opportunities.
"Guests of the festival will be able to immerse themselves in the world of experimental media technologies and learn how innovations in science are becoming a new tool for interacting with art," Elena Zelentsova, Vice President of the Skolkovo Foundation, described the focus of the forum.
Among the participants of Skolkovo Jazz Science 2017 there are many stars, including the Moscow Jazz Orchestra of Igor Butman, which will present a joint program with vocalist Yaroslava Simonova.
Jazz and science are related concepts, and it is no coincidence that they have combined," the People's Artist explained to Izvestia.
Experimentation and improvisation are valued by jazzmen as highly as scientists.
One of the main events of the festival will be the performance of Azekel, a Briton of Nigerian origin, known both for his own work and joint work with the legendary Massive Attack and Gorillaz.
Jazz lovers are looking forward to the first performance in Russia of the five-time Grammy Award nominee, pianist Christian Sands (USA) with his trio.
One of the best academic chamber orchestras "Music of Viva" under the direction of Alexander Rudin and with the participation of pianist Yuri Favorin will try itself in a new capacity.
The fusion of jazz, ethnic and electronic music, as well as academic traditions will be demonstrated by the ensemble "Marimba Plus" and its leader, composer and marimba performer Lea Slepner.
One of the most unusual festival performances promises to be the set of the Sergey Kuryokhin Award winner Anton Maskeliadze.
An experimental artist controls music and video using gestures - this is how leap motion technology works.
A total of eight musical groups will perform on two stages of the festival.
In addition, the program includes open discussions, interactive zones and art objects, united by the idea of merging music and science.
Guests will be able to take part in experiments, visit a scientific buffet and watch the creation of cryogenic or quicksand from starch and water.
In a special vinyl zone, it will be possible to purchase records of actual jazz performers and representatives of other musical directions, and at the book fair - publications on various topics, including music, popular science and biomedical literature.
