In Ukraine, it was proposed to send Russians to prison for illegally crossing the border
The Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine has registered a draft law according to which criminal punishment may appear in the republic for Russians for illegally crossing the Ukrainian border.
According to the RT TV channel, the document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian parliament involves a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens trying to illegally enter the country.
It is noted that for a repeated offense or an act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If the offender was detained at the border with weapons, the time of detention for him will increase to eight years.
Earlier it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians who tried to get to Russia outside the established checkpoints.
