In Russia, there will be two new territories of advanced socio-economic development - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant resolutions of the Government of the Russian Federation will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR on the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia have been determined.
In the city, where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime for entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is assumed that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of types of economic activity in which a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity will operate in the Abaza ASEZ, for example, includes crop production, animal husbandry, food production, soft drinks and clothing.
Already now, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise LLC "Abakan Mine".
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia had fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the ASEZ.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, a territory of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will diversify the economy of the single-industry town, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of JSC Ural Steel, as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 million rubles.
The list of types of economic activity in which a special legal regime for entrepreneurs will operate in the new ASEZ includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first single-industry town in the Orenburg region to receive the status of ASEZ.
Recall that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment and improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the ASEZ are the following: income tax in the amount of not more than 5% for the first five years, and at least 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions in the amount of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, preferential mode of connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rental rates.
