In Moscow, a policeman wounded a man in the leg, defending himself from an attack
A policeman shot a participant in a fight in Moscow in the leg after he attacked him with a piece of glass in his hand.
On August 3, in the evening, the police department of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia in the Yakimanka district received a report of a fight on Mytnaya Street, 46.
"The arriving police squad stopped the offense and separated the participants in the conflict," RIA Novosti reported, citing the press service of the capital's Interior Ministry.
According to the police, when one of the participants in the conflict attacked an employee of the Ministry of Internal Affairs with a piece of glass, the policeman warned the man several times about the use of weapons and fired a warning shot.
This did not stop the bully, after which the law enforcement officer shot the man in the leg.
The injured man needed hospitalization.
